caption.text:
It's funny how the world moves so fast. 
Not so long ago, i was blatantly, remarkably stating that i had fallen. But somehow it felt wrong- i haven’t felt a rush like that in forever. Hustle and bustle, gave it a month, fading- no wonder: lust. 
I had frankly realized, i have notably felt that it was momentary, but i tried hardly to conquer all of those feelings. It was until he did something i would never imagined that eventually had to pierce my blind optimism. Slapped me in the most honest way. I used to believe that people change when given second chance. 
Overlooking that some may not. 
And at some point, i realized that i must stop searching for why.
Leave it be, let it go.
Hustle and bustle.

caption.text: I don't get it, how some people can be really cruel. How some can say they love someone without really meaning it. How you have the heart to hug someone tightly, whisper to her ear that she's nothing less than perfect but decide you don't want her and leaves. How you make her feel like she's on top of the world but then break her heart on the very next day. But she hangs on to all the false hopes you give, still waits for you to change. So to all of you out there who might be feeling what i'm feeling right now: please know that you're worth more. I know he makes butterflies grow in your stomach everytime you see him. He compliments you, kisses you, and tells you that you're beautiful. He gives you all these feelings you swear you've never felt before. And because of those moments, those enchanting moments that you dont want to let go. But let me tell you: you are so much more than a handful of enchanting moments amidst nights of wonder and confusion, amidst his minimal efforts. Stop thinking that he will change. Find someone who sees and accepts you, loves you without any condition, not just in the moment. Someone who will treat you better. Yes, he might be your first in every special things you've ever imagined, and (to my case) he might be your first love, but believe me, the world doesn't stop there. He has never meant to be your last. I know it's hard and i know it hurts. But baby you're worth so much more.
